{"name":"How to Sync Carbs","formula_count":0,"columns":[{"column":"E","hidden":true}],"rows":[{"index":2,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B2","row":2,"column":2,"value":"How to Sync Carbs Using the EMPI Universal Carb Sync Tool (Synchrometer Snail Type P/N: 43-5712-0)†† ","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":23.0}}]},{"index":4,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B4","row":4,"column":2,"value":"1. ","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}},{"coordinate":"C4","row":4,"column":3,"value":"You have to start with a little slack in your cable so that the idle screws are the only thing affecting the RPMs while you sync the idle.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":5,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C5","row":5,"column":3,"value":"In other words if you backed out the idle screws completely the slides should bottom out.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":7,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B7","row":7,"column":2,"value":"2. ","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}},{"coordinate":"C7","row":7,"column":3,"value":"Adjust the idle screws until you get the same reading on both carbs.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":8,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C8","row":8,"column":3,"value":"(The actual number doesn't matter.)","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":10,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B10","row":10,"column":2,"value":"3. ","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}},{"coordinate":"C10","row":10,"column":3,"value":"Once you have the carbs synced at idle; tie a string, zip-tie, rubber-band, Velcro strap, or the likes to keep the throttle about 1/4 open (3-5K rpms).","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":11,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C11","row":11,"column":3,"value":"(Have some cutters nearby incase you get the rpms too high)","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":13,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B13","row":13,"column":2,"value":"4. ","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}},{"coordinate":"C13","row":13,"column":3,"value":"Adjust the carb top cable adjusters until you get the same readings on both carbs.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":14,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C14","row":14,"column":3,"value":"(Again, he actual number doesn't matter.)","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":16,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B16","row":16,"column":2,"value":"5. ","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}},{"coordinate":"C16","row":16,"column":3,"value":"At this point you can remove the implement holding the throttle open and check the cable slack you should have a little free-play between where the throttle is at rest and where it begins to add fuel (about an 1/8\").","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":17,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C17","row":17,"column":3,"value":"Don't forget to slide the rubber boots back down over the cable adjusters.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":19,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C19","row":19,"column":3,"value":"Once this is done your carbs should be in sync.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":21,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C21","row":21,"column":3,"value":"Take it for a spin, if one side comes on before the other just lift the opposite side ever so slightly until they both read the same again.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":23,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B23","row":23,"column":2,"value":"† ","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}},{"coordinate":"C23","row":23,"column":3,"value":"Some YouTube vids by Wes:","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":24,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C24","row":24,"column":3,"value":"HOW TO SYNC BANSHEE CARBS PT1","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":25,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C25","row":25,"column":3,"value":"HOW TO SYNC A STOCK SET OF BANSHEE CARBS AT IDLE","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":26,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C26","row":26,"column":3,"value":"HOW TO SYNC BANSHEE CARBS PT2","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":27,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C27","row":27,"column":3,"value":"HOW TO SYNC A SET OF STOCK BANSHEE CARBS MID THROTTLE","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":29,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B29","row":29,"column":2,"value":"†† ","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}},{"coordinate":"C29","row":29,"column":3,"value":"Here's a YouTube vid by tealakota for syncing without the tool:","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":30,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C30","row":30,"column":3,"value":"How to sync stock carburetors manually on a Yamaha Banshee","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":31,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"C31","row":31,"column":3,"value":"Banshee Carb Syncing","formula":null,